cx.corp.lacuna.core

Interface MemoryReader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemoryReaderImpl

    public interface MemoryReader
    The MemoryReader interface provides methods for reading bytes from the memory of a NativeProcess.
    See Also:
    NativeProcessEnumerator

    • Method Detail

      • readBoolean

        boolean readBoolean(NativeProcess process,
                    int offset)
        Reads an 8-bit boolean value from the specified offset. Any nonzero value will be interpreted as true, whereas zero will be interpreted as false.
        Parameters:
        process - The native process whose memory to read.
        offset - The memory address offset to read from.
        Returns:
        True if the read byte is nonzero, otherwise false.

      • read

        byte[] read(NativeProcess process,
            int offset,
            int bytesToRead)
        Reads a region of memory of the specified NativeProcess.

        This method may return a byte array with fewer elements than bytesToRead. The return value will always be a non-null byte array with a length between 0 and bytesToRead.

        Parameters:
        process - The native process whose memory to read.
        offset - The memory address offset to read from.
        bytesToRead - The amount of bytes to read, starting from the offset.
        Returns:
        The read bytes.
        Throws:
        MemoryReadException - if reading the memory fails.
